  (text "RPi5 INTERFACE NOTES:\n\n40-PIN HEADER (J_GPIO40):\n  STM32U585 signals: 3.3V native, direct routing to header\n  QRB2210 MPU GPIO: 1.8V from JMISC → TXS0108E → 3.3V on header\n  Pins 1,17: +3V3 output (from carrier +3V3 rail)\n  Pins 2,4: +5V output (from carrier +5V rail)\n  Pins 27,28: ID_SD/ID_SC — dedicated I2C to HAT ID EEPROM U_EEPROM\n  NO PCIe: QRB2210 has no PCIe root complex — RPi5 NVMe HATs incompatible\n\nHAT ID EEPROM (U_EEPROM — 24C32):\n  Connected to pins 27 (ID_SD/SDA) and 28 (ID_SC/SCL) exclusively\n  I2C address: 0x50 (A0=A1=A2=GND)\n  Write-protect: ~WP tied to GND (allows programming)\n  4.7kΩ pullups R_E2/R_E3 on ID_SD/ID_SC to +3V3\n  Program with HAT EEPROM utils at first boot\n  Contains: UUID, vendor info, GPIO map, DT overlay reference\n\nCSI CAMERA CONNECTORS:\n  J_CSI0, J_CSI1: 22-pin 0.5mm FPC (Molex 503480-2200)\n  RPi5 camera cable compatible (standard Pi camera ribbon)\n  CCI (I2C): camera control — connect to STM32U585 I2C4 (separate from GPIO bus)\n  +3V3 power to camera module from carrier rail (100mA max per port)\n  All CSI MIPI pairs: 100Ω differential, length-matched"
    (at 20 155 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
)
